[00:08.71]I used to wake up braced for the fall
[00:13.07]Heart racing before nothing at all
[00:17.42]Every quiet felt like a lie
[00:21.78]Peace was a word I didn’t recognize
[00:26.14]But somewhere between the cracks and days
[00:30.49]I noticed the fear didn’t always stay
[00:34.85]I’m not cured, I’m not clean
[00:39.20]But I’m not where I used to be
[00:43.56]I’m learning how to breathe again
[00:47.92]Let the light in, little by little
[00:52.27]I don’t need the armor I lived in
[00:56.63]I’m stronger now, but softer in the middle
[01:00.98]I still shake, but I stand my ground
[01:05.34]I don’t run every time I hear a sound
[01:09.70]I’m not healed, but I’m healing true
[01:14.05]Hope came back when I started choosing me too
[01:18.41]I stopped fighting the scars I wear
[01:22.76]They tell the truth that I’m still here
[01:27.12]I don’t apologize for pacing slow
[01:31.48]Some roads you walk one step at a time alone
[01:35.83]I found peace in the in-between
[01:40.19]In ordinary moments I used to miss
[01:44.54]I still remember, but I don’t drown
[01:48.90]The past lost its grip when I slowed down
[01:53.26]I’m learning how to breathe again
[01:57.61]Trust the calm when it finally settles
[02:01.97]I don’t need to live on edge anymore
[02:06.32]Just to prove that I’m unbreakable
[02:10.68]I still fall, but I rise with grace
[02:15.04]I don’t punish myself for needing space
[02:19.39]I’m not healed, but I’m healing through
[02:23.75]And hope sounds like a voice saying, “You’re allowed to choose you”
[02:28.10]Recovery ain’t a straight line
[02:32.46]Some days I’m brave, some days I hide
[02:36.82]But I don’t call that failure now
[02:41.17]That’s just being alive somehow
[02:45.53]I’m learning how to live again
[02:49.88]Not just survive another season
[02:54.24]I don’t flinch at joy like I used to
[02:58.60]I finally believe I have a reason
[03:02.95]I still carry what shaped my past
[03:07.31]But it doesn’t get to steer my path
[03:11.66]I’m not healed, but I’m healing too
[03:16.02]And hope feels like freedom saying, “You made it through”
[03:20.38]I’m still moving forward…
[03:24.73]And that means everything.
